<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3276] Binary data does not decode correctly using the TJSONProtocol when the base64 encoded data is padded.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3276</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the base64 encoded JSON string has padding bytes at the end, the resulting binary data returned in the thrift object ends up with extra padding bytes (0xFF) at the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like this is caused by the TJSONProtocol &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/0.9.1/lib/java/src/org/apache/thrift/protocol/TJSONProtocol.java#L760&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;using the padded length&lt;/a&gt; when it tries to decode the last chunk, which results in the &apos;=&apos; being converted into binary data.  The DECODE_TABLE defaults to -1 (0xFF), which is how it gets into the final output.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12850009">THRIFT-3276</key>
